From aa4738c1c3c437c0a6538c90fec0a56865210007 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: RivonClaw CI <ci@rivonclaw.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Jul 2026 05:54:47 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] vendor(openclaw): stream Feishu card deltas

Why:
- RivonClaw defaults Feishu QR-created accounts to card streaming, but OpenClaw sent full accumulated snapshots to Feishu CardKit's streaming content endpoint. Feishu appends those fragments, which duplicated partial replies, tool status lines, and final text in long-running conversations.

Removal:
- Drop when upstream OpenClaw's Feishu CardKit streaming adapter sends append-safe deltas, switches to a true replacement API, or otherwise avoids replaying full snapshots during streaming updates.

Tests:
- extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts
---
 .../feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.test.ts       | 126 +++++++++++++++++-
 extensions/feishu/src/reply-dispatcher.ts     |  91 ++++++++++++-
 2 files changed, 206 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

